article.description: Central Connecticut 74, Mount St. Mary's, Md. 68
article.headline: Central Connecticut 74, Mount St. Mary's, Md. 68
article.linkText: Central Connecticut 74, Mount St. Mary's, Md. 68
article.story: NEW BRITAIN, Conn. (AP) -- Obie Nwadike had 20 points and 12 rebounds to lead Central Connecticut to a 74-68 victory over Mount St. Mary's on Sunday, qualifying the Blue Devils for the Northeast Conference championship game. Central Connecticut will face Sacred Heart on Wednesday, and the winner will receive an automatic bid to the NCAA tournament. Jemino Sobers had 20 points for Central Connecticut, including 12 in the second half, to help fight off Mount St. Mary's (11-20). The Blue Devils (21-11) went on a 7-0 run late in the second half to go up 64-59 with five minutes left. Sobers scored five consecutive Blue Devil points during the charge, with Nwadike making the other two. From there, the Blue Devils took over on defense, holding Mount St. Mary's to three field goals over the final 7:47. The game featured seven lead changes and nine ties in the opening 20 minutes, with neither team leading by more than four points. Mount St. Mary's shot 56 percent in the first half (14 for 25), almost all from 12 feet and out. Chris Vann finished with 22 points for the Mountaineers, while Mychal Kearse added 16.
